                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "is this PDO or Mysqli?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-14T17:06:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-14T17:06:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51594",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ignace",
                        "name": "ignace",
                        "displayName": "Ignace",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thank you for looking into this issue.\r\n\r\nI am using PDO. I am using Zend\\Db in a legacy system and init. code goes something like:\r\n\r\n{code}if ($driver instanceof \\PDO) {\r\n  $driver = new Zend\\Db\\Adapter\\Pdo($driver);\r\n}\r\n$adapter = new Adapter($driver);{code}\r\n\r\nI will test this against mysqli driver and report back!\r\n\r\nPS Thank you, and those who contributed, for this wonderful component!\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ignace",
                        "name": "ignace",
                        "displayName": "Ignace",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-15T05:18:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-15T05:27:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51600",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It will fail there too- the problem with mysql is that even though these are values and should technically be capable of being quoted as values, it's not accepting them.  I will have to write some SQL abstraction classes to make this possible.  In the mean time, if you prepare and execute this, it should work.\r\n\r\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
